3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network calculates funding rates every hour based on the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices across its shared order book. The funding mechanism operates independently of traditional CEX rate correlations due to its decentralized nature and multi-chain architecture. Payments are automatically settled between long and short positions, with rates determined by the aggregate demand across all connected frontend partners."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ARB","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ARB/USDT represents significant arbitrage potential as Arbitrum's native token often shows funding rate discrepancies between centralized and decentralized exchanges. The large trading volume and L2 ecosystem dynamics create frequent opportunities for cross-platform arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ARB/USDT funding rates on Orderly Network typically range from -0.1% to 0.3% due to the token's L2 utility and staking demand. Rates often diverge from CEX patterns during Arbitrum ecosystem announcements or governance events. The hourly settlement frequency provides more granular arbitrage windows compared to 8-hour CEX cycles. Peak rate volatility occurs during ARB token unlocks and major DeFi protocol launches on Arbitrum."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-platform arbitrage between Orderly Network and major CEXs like Binance or OKX can yield 0.05-0.2% per funding cycle. The shared liquidity model creates unique opportunities when one frontend partner experiences high demand while others remain balanced. Multi-chain accessibility allows for efficient capital deployment across NEAR and EVM-compatible networks. Traders can exploit rate differentials by monitoring Orderly's funding against traditional exchanges during high volatility periods."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network's dependency on frontend partners creates execution risk if primary interfaces experience downtime or liquidity fragmentation. Bridge delays between NEAR and EVM chains can impact arbitrage timing, especially during network congestion. The platform's 0.02% maker and 0.05% taker fees must be factored into arbitrage calculations alongside gas costs. Smart contract risks inherent to DEX infrastructure require careful position sizing and monitoring of protocol updates."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ARB/USDT funding rates updated on Orderly Network?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and settled every hour on Orderly Network, providing 24 settlement cycles per day. This hourly frequency allows for more responsive rate adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"Can I access ARB/USDT perpetuals through multiple frontends on Orderly?","answer":"Yes, Orderly Network's shared liquidity infrastructure allows access through various DEX frontends built on their protocol. All frontends share the same order book and funding rates, but may offer different user interfaces and additional features."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for ARB/USDT perpetuals on Orderly Network?","answer":"Orderly Network charges 0.02% for maker orders and 0.05% for taker orders on ARB/USDT perpetuals. These fees are competitive with major DEXs and must be considered when calculating funding rate arbitrage profitability."},{"question":"How does Orderly Network's multi-chain support affect ARB trading?","answer":"Orderly's NEAR and EVM compatibility allows traders to deposit collateral from multiple chains, potentially reducing bridging costs for ARB positions. However, cross-chain operations may introduce settlement delays that could impact time-sensitive arbitrage strategies."}]}]
